21:13.326 --> 21:14.128
What a good thought.

21:14.548 --> 21:16.772
And if you put it under his story, okay, God, you put this number in my heart.

21:16.792 --> 21:17.833
I'm gonna put seed in the ground.

21:18.094 --> 21:19.957
God, I'm gonna watch you make it happen.

21:20.157 --> 21:22.300
And then he has authority to bless your life.

21:22.320 --> 21:23.121
He has all authority.

21:23.181 --> 21:25.845
Secondly, Jesus' heart is for all people.

21:26.607 --> 21:26.927
Look at it.

21:27.147 --> 21:30.833
Go in, therefore, and make disciples of all nations.

21:31.694 --> 21:34.098
God's heart is for lost people everywhere.

21:35.522 --> 21:38.386
God's heart breaks for the lost.

21:39.869 --> 21:42.072
He cares about lost people in Springfield.

21:42.813 --> 21:45.136
He cares about lost people in Joplin.

21:45.156 --> 21:46.799
He cares about lost people in Missouri.

21:46.839 --> 21:48.782
He cares about lost people in the U.S.

21:49.483 --> 21:56.253
He cares about lost people in Ethiopia and Thailand and France because God's heart is for the lost.

21:56.574 --> 22:01.862
The Son of Man came to seek and save those who are lost.

22:02.623 --> 22:04.786
That's why this moment is so

22:04.962 --> 22:06.384
incredibly important.

22:07.747 --> 22:10.210
Because Jesus' heart is for all people.

22:10.691 --> 22:13.856
